title: Federal rail cash under a cloud over South Yarra station stoush
text:
Federal rail cash under a cloud over ... Federal rail cash under a cloud over South Yarra station stoush Next Story Prev Story 4 hrs ago Read more: The Age 
Federal cash for the Melbourne Metro Rail tunnel is under a cloud because of a refusal by the Andrews government to include a $1 billion new station at South Yarra. Prime Minister Malcolm Turnbull is being vigorously lobbied by senior colleagues furious over an Andrews Government decision to bypass the station by just meters to avoid a claimed $970 million cost blowout and an additional 100 property acquisitions.   The Age.
